snippet.textDisplay:
There's actually a few ways you can get money specifically.

- YouTube: YouTube pays you for each video once you've reached 1k subs, based on numerous factors; views, like to dislike ratio, views to subs ratio, length of the video which goes into the last factor; ad revenue. But if the content is deemed inappropriate or copyright or somehow offensive, it is demonetised.

Donations: This is mostly for streamers, but as you stream, your viewers can tip you or donate if you prefer, and the streaming service takes I think 5% of the tip, but the rest is given to you. Ninja never gets less than a thousand dollars per stream from tips.

Sponsorships: Sometimes game producers, brands and so on will give you money to endorse their product in your videos. Kevin Hart did this in this video with that antiperspirant.

Merchandise: You can link up with a manufacturer who can make you merchandise for your channel; hats, shirts, gaming equipment etc. And you get money from each individual item sale.

Tournaments: Big prize pools, if you're a pro gamer, you can try out for these tournaments, which are livestreamed, and if you come first, you'll win a few million dollars.
